# Shortest Path in an Undirected Graph

| | |
| :--- | :--- |
| **Input** | Standard input |
| **Output** | Standard output |

### Problem Statement
Find the length of the shortest path between two specified vertices in an undirected graph.

### Input Format
- The first line contains the number of vertices $N$ ($1 \le N \le 100$).
- The following $N$ lines contain the adjacency matrix (where `0` denotes the absence of an edge and `1` denotes its presence).
- The last line contains the indices of the start and end vertices.

### Output Format
Print the length $L$ of the shortest path (the number of edges). If no path exists, print `-1`.

### Examples
| Input | Output |
| :--- | :--- |
| `5` <br> `0 1 0 0 1` <br> `1 0 1 0 0` <br> `0 1 0 0 0` <br> `0 0 0 0 0` <br> `1 0 0 0 0` <br> `3 5` | `3` |

#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

int main() {
    int N;
    cin >> N;
    
    int graph[100][100];
    for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
        for (int j = 0; j < N; j++) {
            cin >> graph[i][j];
        }
    }
    
    int s, e;
    cin >> s >> e;
    
    s--;
    e--;
    
    if (s == e) {
        cout << "0" << endl;
        return 0;
    }
    
    int queue[100];
    int visited[100];
    int dist[100];
    
    int q_start = 0, q_end = 0;
    
    queue[q_end++] = s;
    visited[s] = 1;
    dist[s] = 0;
    
    while (q_start < q_end) {
        int current = queue[q_start++];
        
        for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
            if (graph[current][i] == 1 && !visited[i]) {
                if (i == e) {
                    cout << dist[current] + 1 << endl;
                    return 0;
                }
                
                queue[q_end++] = i;
                visited[i] = 1;
                dist[i] = dist[current] + 1;
            }
        }
    }
    
    cout << "-1" << endl;
    
    return 0;
}


# 1. Shortest Path with Reconstruction (Восстановление пути)

| | |
| :--- | :--- |
| **Input** | Standard input |
| **Output** | Standard output |

### Problem Statement
In an undirected graph, find the shortest path between two given vertices. You need to output both the length of the path and the sequence of vertices.

### Input Format
- The first line contains the number of vertices $N$ ($1 \le N \le 100$).
- The following $N$ lines contain the adjacency matrix (where `0` denotes the absence of an edge and `1` denotes its presence).
- The last line contains the indices of the start and end vertices.

### Output Format
- First, print the length $L$ of the shortest path (the number of edges).
- If $L > 0$, print the path as a sequence of vertex indices on the next line.
- If the length is $0$ (start and end are the same), output only the length.
- If no path exists, print `-1`.

### Examples
| Input | Output |
| :--- | :--- |
| `5` <br> `0 1 0 0 1` <br> `1 0 1 0 0` <br> `0 1 0 0 0` <br> `0 0 0 0 0` <br> `1 0 0 0 0` <br> `3 5` | `3` <br> `3 2 1 5` |

#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

int main() {
    int N;
    cin >> N;
    
    int graph[100][100];
    for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
        for (int j = 0; j < N; j++) {
            cin >> graph[i][j];
        }
    }
    
    int start, end;
    cin >> start >> end;
    start--;
    end--;
    
    if (start == end) {
        cout << 0 << endl;
        return 0;
    }
    
    int queue[10000];
    int front = 0, back = 0;
    
    bool visited[100] = {false};
    int distance[100] = {0};
    int parent[100];
    
    for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
        parent[i] = -1;
    }
    
    queue[back++] = start;
    visited[start] = true;
    distance[start] = 0;
    
    bool found = false;
    
    while (front < back) {
        int current = queue[front++];
        
        if (current == end) {
            found = true;
            break;
        }
        
        for (int neighbor = 0; neighbor < N; neighbor++) {
            if (graph[current][neighbor] == 1 && !visited[neighbor]) {
                queue[back++] = neighbor;
                visited[neighbor] = true;
                distance[neighbor] = distance[current] + 1;
                parent[neighbor] = current;
            }
        }
    }
    
    if (!found) {
        cout << -1 << endl;
        return 0;
    }
    
    cout << distance[end] << endl;
    
    if (distance[end] > 0) {
        int path[100];
        int path_length = 0;
        int current = end;
        
        while (current != -1) {
            path[path_length++] = current + 1;
            current = parent[current];
        }
        
        for (int i = path_length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
            cout << path[i] << " ";
        }
        cout << endl;
    }
    
    return 0;
}
